children.subject: It is possible to take 20 and 40 at the same time. You'd need to fill out both google forms. It is also possible to take 40 this summer (which is far less impacted) and 20 in fall. What year are you? EE 16A will be far less impacted in Spring.

I'm currently a freshman but I'm studying abroad in Spring (because ME electives aren't offered at places I'd want to go). I also already committed to (and paid for) things this summer. Therefore, I would only be able to take 16A in my junior year, and taking 106AB, 120, and 128 all in my senior year would be difficult.

Also, if I remove all unnecessary courses from telebears, I'll only have 7.5 units in phase 1 (I need 3 units for ME85). Would I still be able to get onto the lists for both 20 and 40?

Would I be able to meet with you or another EE advisor and hash a workable schedule out?

You are welcome to set some time to talk to me: sarahvannostrand.youcanbook.me

or Sara Nevius: saranevius.youcanbook.me

:)
